-- Greenhill Hires Credit Suisse’s Vikram Gandhi as Senior Adviser
-- B y   S t e v e   D i c k s o n
-- 2012-03-06T12:40:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/greenhill-hires-credit-suisse-s-vikram-gandhi-as-senior-adviser.html
Greenhill & Co., the advisory firm
founded by Robert Greenhill, hired Vikram Gandhi as a senior
adviser focusing on  India  and Asia.  Gandhi was most recently global head of the financial
institutions group at  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN) , and spent 16 years
at Morgan Stanley, New York-based Greenhill said today in a
statement.  “With the addition of someone of Vikram’s caliber we gain
access to important potential clients in India,” Greenhill
Chief Executive Officer Scott Bok said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
